    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbstractGameController
    Abstract base controller for all game modes using Template Method Pattern.
    ColorValue
    UI-agnostic color value used by the model layer.
    Game
    Tron game entry program (JavaFX launcher) Responsibilities: initialize stage, load main menu, configure window
    GameArea
    Game area abstract base class (parent class for all game mode canvases) Encapsulates Canvas initialization, background drawing, common reset logic
    GameConstant
    Global constants in tron_master
    GameData
    Game shared data model (Singleton pattern: globally unique, accessible by all controllers/views) Stores global data such as scores, levels, settings, etc.
    GameLogic
    Class for handling game logic (player collision, player operation effect â€“> boost and jump, score-related logic)
    GameObject
    Base class for renderable/movable game entities.
    GameObjectFactory
    Factory class for creating GameObject instances (currently Player types).
    GameObjectFactory.GameObjectType
    GameObject type enumeration for type-safe object creation.
    GameState
    Game state enumeration Define the possible states of the game
    HighScoreDialogController
    Controller for high score display.
    HighScoreManager
    Model class for managing high scores.
    HighScoreManager.GameMode
    Game mode enum for high score tracking.
    HighScoreManager.ScoreEntry
    High score entry containing score and mode.
    InstructionsController
    Controller for the instructions dialog window.
    Intersection
    The results of an intersection test: no intersection, or the direction in which the intersection happened.
    Line
    View layer line class for rendering.
    LineSegment
    Represents a line segment defined by two endpoints.
    MainMenuController
    Controller for the main menu scene.
    Player
    Abstract base class for all player types.
    PlayerAI
    AI-controlled player implementation.
    PlayerController
    Controller class for handling player input and connect view layer for rendering
    PlayerHuman
    Human-controlled player implementation.
    PlayerRenderer
    View class responsible for rendering Player objects.
    PlayerStateListener
    Observer interface for listening to object state changes.
    PlayMenuController
    Controller for the mode selection (play) menu.
    Portal
    A portal wall that teleports players to a linked exit portal instead of killing them.
    SettingsController
    Settings controller: currently handles background color selection for the game canvas.
    Shape
    Shape drawn on the game court.
    SoundEffectListener
    Sound effect listener that triggers audio feedback for player state changes.
    SoundManager
    Singleton sound manager for handling game audio (sound effects and background music).
    StoryGameController
    Controller for story mode game scene.
    StoryLogicStrategy
    Game logic strategy for Story mode.
    StoryViewStrategy
    Story mode game view (manages FXML loading, UI components, and game canvas)
    SurvivalGameController
    Controller for survival mode game scene.
    SurvLogicStrategy
    Game logic strategy for Survival mode.
    SurvViewStrategy
    Survival mode game view (manages FXML loading, UI components, and game canvas)
    TwoPlayerGameController
    Controller for two-player mode game scene.
    TwoPlayerLogicStrategy
    Game logic strategy for Two-Player mode.
    TwoPlayerOutcome
    Outcome of a two-player match.
    TwoPlayerViewStrategy
    Two-player mode game view (manages FXML loading, UI components, and game canvas)
    ViewUtils
    View utility class: create image buttons, load images, common UI configurations
    Wall
    Represents a static wall (obstacle) in the game area.
    WallLayoutController
    Loads wall and portal layouts from FXML files designed in SceneBuilder.
    WallRenderer
    Renders wall objects on the game canvas.
